Qualifying Human Activity

Click Here to see the Notebook online in Jupyter nbviewer.

Notebook testing various classification algorithms on accelerometer data to qualify how individuals perform weight-lifting exercises

The best performing algorithms are a K-Nearest and a GBM Classifier with over 99.9% accuracy, precision, recall, and F1 on 5 classes.

The data comes from Veloso et al., (2013). The original dataset and more information can be found here. The direct link to download the data is found here.

Contents:

  • qualifying_workouts.ipynb: Jupyter notebook with the Python code to process the data, the algorithms, and report.
  • cm_heat_plots.py: A Python script with functions to plot the confusion matrices
  • confusion_matrixGBM.png: An output image.
  • README.md: This File
